Problem statement
1. You are responsible for improving the On-Boarding experience and educating the user about the platform
2. You should be able to guide the user to the aha moment of creating a project from scratch and sharing with the
team
3. The user has a migration challenge of moving from current platforms like Notion to Zeda.io

Approach
1. Educate users about the platform, thereby increasing Product Adoption & improving Onboarding
experience
2. Since 23% of leading causes of churn is contributed by poor onboarding, it is essential to guide the users

What is Zeda?
Zeda is a Product Management suite that brings all the things needed to
define, manage, & collaborate on your product at one place. Zeda provides a
centralised space to your Product Managers and team to improve work
efficiency and in turn go from idea to shipping the product faster.

550k $
Founded year
2021

Solution 4 - Onboarding checklist
Current
Suggestion
Currently, Zeda sends out a welcome
email along with a checklist to get started.
User onboarding checklist on Zeda
homepage could potentially increase the
motivation of users to complete crucial
steps by breaking bigger tasks into
smaller ones
Checklist helps set user expectations and encourages progress.
Checklists offer a visual representation of an unfinished task and inform
the user how far away they are from completing it. For example, Zeda
checklist can consist of tasks like
1. Create your first product
2. Create your PRD
3. Add members & etc.
A progress bar
displays Users stage
during Onboarding
Solution 5 - Gamification
Suggestion
To gamify checklists, we can
provide an incentive for the
users as and when they tick off
tasks from their checklist. Add
vouchers on their plan for a
prompt completion of each task
The discount code should only appear once they tick
off their checklist tasks.
Complete each task below
to avail 20% off your
subscription!

Bonus Solutions -
Trigger a celebratory notification to go off once a user hits a milestone. This can delight your
customers, boosts engagement, & improves retention.
Measure CSAT throughout the Onboarding( Trigger a CSAT survey after every milestone
achieved by the customer, ex: After successfully completing Migration process). This can
provide you more information on whether the user enjoys that particular feature or not.
